# PyBayfile
PyBayfile is a Python module for handling bayfiles
bayfiles is a website that allows users to upload and share files

## exmaple of usage:
```python
from PyBayfile import Archive

# make the archive
path = './etc/file_to_upload.exe'
archive: Archive = Archive.make_from_path(path)

# print the link of the archive: link is str(archive) or archive.link
print(f'your file is uploaded to: {archive} and the size is {archive.size} bytes')
```

## Bayfile class (Archive)
__attributes__
| name | value
| --- | --- |
| .url | the short url of the bayfile
| .long_url | the long url of the bayfile
| .id | the ID of the bayfile
| .name | the name of the bayfile
| .size | the size of the bayfile's content in bytes
| .api_data | the data that returned the API

__class methods__
| name | usage
| --- | --- |
| make_from_path | create a Bayfile from the file path
| make_from_text | create a Bayfile with the given text in it
| from_id | get a bayfile by his ID
| from_url | get a bayfile by his URL


